{"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"addToggleRef","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"notify","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GToggleNotify","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gobject.h@T@GToggleNotify"},{"text":"?, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"data","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil)"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This functionality is intended for binding ","type":"text"},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to a proxy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"object managed by another memory manager. This is done with two","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"paired references: the strong reference added by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and a reverse reference to the proxy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"object which is either a strong reference or weak reference."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The setup is that when there are no other references to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"only a weak reference is held in the reverse direction from ","type":"text"},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to the proxy object, but when there are other references held to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", a strong reference is held. The "},{"code":"notify","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" callback is called","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"when the reference from "},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to the proxy object should be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"“toggled” from strong to weak (","type":"text"},{"code":"is_last_ref","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" true) or weak to strong","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"("},{"code":"is_last_ref","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" false)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since a (normal) reference must be held to the object before"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calling "},{"code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", the initial state of the reverse"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"link is always strong.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Multiple toggle references may be added to the same gobject,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"however if there are multiple toggle references to an object, none","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of them will ever be notified until all but one are removed.  For"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this reason, you should only ever use a toggle reference if there"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is important state in the proxy object.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that if you unref the object on another thread, then "},{"code":"notify","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" might"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"still be invoked after "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_remove_toggle_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":", and the object argument"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"might be a dangling pointer. If the object is destroyed on other threads,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"you must take care of that yourself.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":" must be released with "},{"code":"g_object_remove_toggle_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Increases the reference count of the object by one and sets a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"callback to be called when all other references to the object are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"dropped, or when this is already the last reference to the object"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and another reference is established."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"title":"addToggleRef(notify:data:)","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"GLibObject","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"addToggleRef","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"notify","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GToggleNotify","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gobject.h@T@GToggleNotify"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"text":"data","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?)"}],"externalID":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolPAAE12addToggleRef6notify4datayySvSg_SpySo8_GObjectVGSgs5Int32VtXCSg_AGtF::SYNTHESIZED::s:10GLibObject0B0C"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/object\/addtoggleref(notify:data:)"]}],"